 the hard resist in melee.  <BR>  <BR> We'll figure out how this zone work =)  <BR>  <BR> Krelian Lionheart - 50 Shaman on E'ci  <BR> Survivor of a 7 mobs train in Hate  <BR> Victim of a 16 mob train in Hate  <BR>  <BR>                      . <BR> seaen <BR> Unregistered User <BR> (1/8/00 4:06:11 pm) <BR> Reply <BR> whats up with rangers? <BR>  <BR> well after doing Hate last night, i reaized hate is not al that worth it for us. 1st we only have 2 items in hate, one being the reve whip< its a ok weapon some like it better then the ykehsa, we have been doing hate every day for a week straid only one whip so far, second item is a sword droped by inn well its a kick ass sword but he only drops one, and hes like a 10 day spawn, so hope you win the roll.  Rangers are just good dmg, my group(ranger(me)druid, enchanter, bard, cleric, and rogue took like 90% of the kills, i walked out of hate with no gain at all, you are gona die it happens Hate is a bugged zone. Meastro attacked me first when we pulled him, he hit me for solit 200's till i was dead, cleric couldnt heal fast enough after that he was jumping all over killing casters... not a good thing had to CR. we will try again to night hopefully with more sucess.  <BR>  <BR> Seaen  <BR> 47 ranger of Tunare <BR>  <BR>  <BR> Bean <BR> Unregistered User <BR> (1/9/00 8:11:36 am) <BR> Reply <BR> Re: whats up with rangers? <BR>  <BR> What a crazy mixed up bunch you are.  <BR>  <BR> Dracholiche  <BR> Maestro  <BR> Lord Nagafen  <BR> Lady Vox  <BR> Cazic Thule  <BR> Innoruuk  <BR>  <BR> That is without a doubt the silliest list of hardest to easiest I have ever seen. There are NO opinions on this matter, the list is:  <BR>  <BR> Lord Nagafen  <BR> Lady Vox  <BR> Dracoliche  <BR> Innoruuk  <BR> Maestro  <BR> Cazic Thule  <BR>  <BR> I don't see how you can not see that...but then again I'm reading a thread with waving tactics written all over it. People, you can do Vox with 18 people and suffer minimal casualties. You can fight Ca